All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Application
    This abstract class describes an Application or a usecase for a NeuralNetwork, and its subclasses acts as a way to train a NeuralNetwork in a there specified Application or usecase using the AppliedNetwork class.
    AppliedNetwork
    This class is used to simplify the usage of a NeuralNetwork by combineing it with an Application describing how the NeuralNetwork should be trained ect.
    BiasNeuron
    This is an extension of Neuron used to represent bias in a NeuronBasedNeuralNetwork.
    InnerNeuron
    This is an extension of Neuron.
    InnerNeuronLayer
    This is an extension of Layer and is used as InnerLayers (Layers in between the first (Input) and the last (Output)) in a NeuronBasedNeuralNetwork.
    InputNeuron
    This is an extension of Neuron, used to represent the Neurons in the first Layer (InputLayer) in a NeuronBasedNeuralNetwork.
    InputNeuronLayer
    This is an extension of Layer and is used as an InputLayer (the first Layer) in a NeuronBasedNeuralNetwork.
    LayerD
    This abstract class heavily outlines the functionality of a layer in a NeuralNetwork, using double as its basic calculation unit.
    LayerF
    This abstract class heavily outlines the functionality of a layer in a NeuralNetwork, using float as its basic calculation unit.
    LayerInnerD
    Subclass of LayerD, used as the hidden (inner) layers of a NeuralNetwork.
    LayerInnerF
    Subclass of LayerF, used as the hidden (inner) layers of a NeuralNetwork.
    LayerInputD
    Subclass of LayerD, used as the input (first) layer of a NeuralNetwork.
    LayerInputF
    Subclass of LayerF, used as the input (first) layer of a NeuralNetwork.
    LayerOutputD
    Subclass of LayerF, used as the hidden (inner) layers of a NeuralNetwork.
    LayerOutputF
    Subclass of LayerF, used as the hidden (inner) layers of a NeuralNetwork.
    MainXOR
    Basic test of the neural network to see if it can learn how a XOR-gate works.
    MatrixOperations
    Simple class defining some simple matrix operations such as matrix multiplication (dot-product) of two float[][] or two double[][[]
    Mnist
    Implementation of Application, contains basic methods needed to train a NeuralNetwork on the Mnist dataset of handwritten digits.
    MnistDataVisualizer
    This is a simple class that displays data downloaded from the Mnist website in a JFrame.
    MnistFileReader
    This is a class that reads the idx1-ubyte/idx3-ubyte files that can be downloaded at the Mnist website (http://yann.lecun.com/exdb/mnist/) and returns them as float[][] or double[][], where the first index represents the set of training data and the second index represents which part of that data.
    NeuralNetwork
    This is an interface containing the basic abstract methods needed in order to operate a NeuralNetwork.
    NeuralNetworkD
    NeuralNetworkF is a simple implementation of a neural network using matrices.
    NeuralNetworkF
    NeuralNetworkF is a simple implementation of a neural network using matrices.
    Neuron
    This is a simple abstract class describing a Neuron in a NeuronBasedNeuralNetwork, and has several subclasses with different Neurons.
    NeuronBasedNeuralNetwork
    A Precursor to NeuralNetwork using instances of the Neuron class and its subclasses instead of matrices.
    NeuronLayer
    This abstract class contain all basic methods and attributes of a Neuron based Layer.
    OutputNeuron
    This is an extension of Neuron, used to represent the Neurons in the last Layer (OutputLayer) of a NeuronBasedNeuralNetwork.
    OutputNeuronLayer
    This is an extension of Layer and is used as OutputLayers (the last Layer) in a NeuronBasedNeuralNetwork.
    XOR
    Contains all specific XOR-Gate related methods.
    XorGate
    Implementation of Application, contains basic methods needed to train a NeuralNetwork on a XOR Gate.
    XorGateDataGenerator
    An abstract class to hold a few static methods for generating trainingdata for a NeuralNetwork in the Xor Gate Application.
    XORSuccessRate
    Tests the success rate of training a neural network to function as a XOR-gate.
